This paper discusses the strengths and weaknesses of the arXiv, which is a preprint repository for scientific articles. The paper focuses on the use of new technologies to improve the arXiv, which suggests that it is related to computer science. Specifically, the paper discusses the use of document creation and dissemination technologies, which suggests that it is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses cultural practices related to collaboration and data sharing, which suggests that it is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the history of research communication and the Web, which suggests that it is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
